{"parse":{"title":"Higan","pageid":4495257,"revid":849914173,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><dl><dd><i>For the multi-system <a href=\"/wiki/Video_game_console_emulator\" title=\"Video game console emulator\">emulator</a>, see <a href=\"/wiki/Higan_(emulator)\" title=\"Higan (emulator)\">higan (emulator)</a>. For the fictional <a href=\"/wiki/Video_game\" title=\"Video game\">video game</a> protagonist, see <a href=\"/wiki/Far_East_of_Eden_Zero\" title=\"Far East of Eden Zero\">Far East of Eden Zero</a>.</i></dd></dl>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Refimprove\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>needs additional citations for <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">verification</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\" title=\"Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1\">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.</span>  <small><i>(September 2010)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau,_Hidaka,_Saitama.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg/220px-Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"142\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg/330px-Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg/440px-Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau%2C_Hidaka%2C_Saitama.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2650\" data-file-height=\"1713\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lycoris_radiata_-_Kinchakuda_Plateau,_Hidaka,_Saitama.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>In Japan the <a href=\"/wiki/Red_spider_lily\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red spider lily\">red spider lily</a> signals <a href=\"/wiki/Sh%C5%ABbun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sh\u016bbun\">sh\u016bbun</a>, the arrival of <a href=\"/wiki/Fall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fall\">fall</a>.  Many <a href=\"/wiki/Buddhist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Buddhist\">Buddhists</a> will use it to celebrate the arrival of fall with a ceremony at the <a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_cemeteries_and_cenotaphs\" title=\"Japanese cemeteries and cenotaphs\">tomb of one of their ancestors</a>.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Higan</b><span style=\"font-weight: normal\">&#32;(<span lang=\"ja\">\u5f7c\u5cb8</span>)</span> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Buddhist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Buddhist\">Buddhist</a> holiday exclusively celebrated by Japanese sects during both the Spring and Autumnal <a href=\"/wiki/Equinox\" title=\"Equinox\">Equinox</a>.  It is observed by nearly every Buddhist school in Japan.  The tradition extends from mild weather that occurs during the time of equinoxes, though the origin of the holiday dates from <a href=\"/wiki/Emperor_Sh%C5%8Dmu\" title=\"Emperor Sh\u014dmu\">Emperor Sh\u014dmu</a> in the 8th century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  People who normally worked in the fields had more leisure time to evaluate their own practices, and to make a renewed effort to follow Buddhism.  Today, special services are usually observed in Japanese Buddhist temples, and Japanese temples abroad, based on the particular Buddhist tradition or sect.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Origin\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Origin</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Ancestral_veneration\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ancestral veneration</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origin\">Origin</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Origin\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The etymology of <i>Ohigan</i> is from \"the other shore of the <a href=\"/wiki/Sanzu_River\" title=\"Sanzu River\">Sanzu River</a>\", which separates this life from the afterlife in <a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_Buddhism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Japanese Buddhism\">Japanese Buddhist tradition</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ancestral_veneration\">Ancestral veneration</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Ancestral veneration\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Similar to <a href=\"/wiki/Obon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Obon\">Obon</a>, Japanese people will often return to their hometowns during the holiday season to pay respects to their ancestors. Ohigan is a public holiday, thus many businesses are closed.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://la.nichirenshu.org/teachings/talks/3min/middle_way_higan.htm\">\"Middle Way &amp; Higan Service, Nichiren Shu Beikoku Betsuin\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-04-10</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Middle+Way+%26+Higan+Service%2C+Nichiren+Shu+Beikoku+Betsuin&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fla.nichirenshu.org%2Fteachings%2Ftalks%2F3min%2Fmiddle_way_higan.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHigan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Lycoris_(plant)\" title=\"Lycoris (plant)\">Lycoris (plant)</a> - In Japanese, <i>higan-bana</i> (higan-flower)</li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:HakoneFestival0028.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/HakoneFestival0028.jpg/30px-HakoneFestival0028.jpg\" width=\"30\" height=\"23\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/HakoneFestival0028.jpg/45px-HakoneFestival0028.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/HakoneFestival0028.jpg/60px-HakoneFestival0028.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"750\" data-file-height=\"563\" /></a></td><td><i>This article related to a Japanese festival or holiday is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Higan&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Japan-festival-stub\" title=\"Template:Japan-festival-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Japan-festival-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Japan-festival-stub\"><abbr title=